<h2>
<font color="#0F75FF">
Suggested Calibrations for Echelette Mode
</font></h2>
<hr></center></b>

<p>


</p>
<H3><font color="Red"> I. Bias Frames</font></h3>

<h4>
<ul>

 <li> Problem: There is 2D structure in the bias frames which is not fully 
accounted for by the overscan region
<font color="Green"> 
 <li> Solution: Take 10 exposures per binning setup
</font>
 <li> Alternate Solution: Use an archived bias frame [known to be ok]
</ul>
</h4>
<hr>

<p>


</p>
<H3><font color="Red"> II. Flats </font></h3>

<h4>
<ul>

 <li> Problem: There is significant scattered light with the internal flats
<font color="Green"> 
 <li> Solution: Take >5 dome flats per slit width (note this is time consuming)
</font>
 <li> Alternate Solution: Use an archived flat  [not well tested]
</ul>
</h4>
<hr>

<p>


</p>
<H3><font color="Red"> III. Arcs </font></h3>

<h4>
<ul>

 <li> Problem: All of the lamps are needed to get a solution across the entire wavelength range
 <li> Problem: There isn't a lot of signal in some important CuAr lines
<font color="Green"> 
 <li> Solution: Take exposures with all lamps on (start with all on and turn of Hg,Xe)
 <li> Solution: Take multiple arc exposures (5 ideally per slit width)
</font>
 <li> Alternate Solution: Use an archived arc [not well tested]
</ul>
</h4>
<hr>

</p>
<H3><font color="Red"> IV.  Order Curvature</font></h3>

<h4>
<ul>

 <li> Issue: The orders are significantly curved in the data images
<font color="Green"> 
 <li> Solution: Take exposures with the multi-holes slit
</font>
 <li> Problem: Tough to get sufficient flux in cornes of the CCD
<font color="Green"> 
 <li> Solution: Take several exposures during twilight
</font>
 <li> Alternate Solution: Use an archived map [works well]
</ul>
</h4>
